          "edits": [
            [
              {
                "text": "# Media Bias Pipeline\n\nEnd-to-end data pipeline that produces a fine-tuning-ready dataset for a **media bias classifier**, covering text + image content. Built as a PhD technical exam deliverable (~4–6h scope).\n\n## Sub-task (to be finalized)\nA single, measurable bias sub-task selected from a published media bias survey, measurable in both text and image (e.g., *opinion-vs-fact framing*, *sentiment-laden language*, *loaded image framing*). Justification lives in the final report section below.\n\n## Pipeline\n\n```\ncrawl  ->  sentence_split  ->  proxy_label  ->  annotate_llm\n                                            \\-> annotate_vlm\n                                             -> analyze (EDA + agreement)\n```\n\n| Stage | Script | Output |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1. Crawl 100–300 articles | `src/crawl.py` | `data/raw/html/`, `data/processed/articles.jsonl` |\n| 2. Clean + sentence split | `src/sentence_split.py` | `data/processed/sentences.jsonl` |\n| 3. Proxy classifier (HF) | `src/proxy_label.py` | `data/processed/proxy_predictions.jsonl` |\n| 4. LLM annotation (50–100) | `src/annotate_llm.py` | `data/processed/llm_annotations.jsonl` |\n| 5. VLM annotation (images) | `src/annotate_vlm.py` | `data/processed/vlm_annotations.jsonl` |\n| 6. EDA + agreement | `src/analyze.py`, `notebooks/eda.ipynb` | `data/analysis/` |\n\n## Repo layout\n\n```\nmedia-bias-pipeline/\n├── ai_usage/step_logs.md          # append-only AI-assistant log (per step)\n├── data/{raw,processed,analysis}/ # crawled + derived data\n├── prompts/                       # LLM & VLM prompt templates\n├── src/                           # pipeline scripts\n└── notebooks/eda.ipynb            # exploratory analysis\n```\n\n## Setup\n\n```powershell\npython -m venv .venv; .\\.venv\\Scripts\\Activate.ps1\npip install -r requirements.txt\nCopy-Item .env.example .env       # fill in keys if needed\n```\n\n## Run\n\n```powershell\npython src/crawl.py\npython src/sentence_split.py\npython src/proxy_label.py\npython src/annotate_llm.py\npython src/annotate_vlm.py\npython src/analyze.py\n```\n\n## AI usage policy\nEvery step the assistant takes is logged forward-only to [ai_usage/step_logs.md](ai_usage/step_logs.md). No retroactive edits. The rule is enforced via [CLAUDE.md](CLAUDE.md).\n\n## Report (to be filled)\n- **Chosen sub-task & justification** — TBD\n- **Pipeline overview** — see diagram above\n- **Decisions & trade-offs** — TBD\n- **Proxy classifier fit & expected disagreement** — TBD\n- **Shortcuts & risks** — TBD\n- **AI usage summary** — see `ai_usage/step_logs.md`\n",
