      "requestId": "request_bd5144a4-94e7-4d3c-8f19-e90078e3e594",
      "message": {
        "text": "Update the repo:\r\nProject goal:\r\nBuild a small end-to-end pipeline that produces a fine-tuning-ready dataset for sentence-level media bias detection.\r\n\r\nChosen sub-task:\r\nSentence-level subjective / opinionated framing bias in English news articles.\r\n\r\nCollection target:\r\n- Total: 300 articles.\r\n- 150 articles from left-leaning outlet block.\r\n- 150 articles from right-leaning outlet block.\r\n- Use RSS feeds.\r\n- The implementation can choose the outlets itself, but must document which outlets were used and why.\r\n- Outlet block labels are exploratory metadata, not ground truth ideology labels.\r\n\r\nCore pipeline:\r\nRSS feeds\r\n→ article URL collection\r\n→ article extraction\r\n→ article-level dataset\r\n→ sentence-level dataset\r\n→ Hugging Face proxy subjectivity labeling\r\n→ LLM sentence annotation\r\n→ VLM image annotation\r\n→ EDA + agreement analysis\r\n→ README report\r\n\r\nImportant unit choices:\r\n- Collection unit = article.\r\n- Text fine-tuning unit = sentence.\r\n- VLM unit = article main image + title/lead.\r\n- Proxy classifier input = sentence only.\r\n- Source, outlet block, title, URL, and image URL are metadata.\r\n\r\nProxy model:\r\nUse GroNLP/mdebertav3-subjectivity-multilingual for proxy labels.\r\nIt outputs OBJ/SUBJ and is used as a proxy for subjective/opinionated framing, not as a complete media bias detector.\r\n\r\nLLM model:\r\nUse OpenAI model ID: gpt-5.4-mini.\r\nBefore implementing API calls, check official OpenAI docs for the correct model name, supported endpoints, image input support, context window, and output limits.\r\nDo not design the final LLM annotation prompt yet. Prompt design will be handled later.\r\n\r\nToken/context requirement:\r\nThe OpenAI docs list gpt-5.4-mini with a 400,000-token context window and 128,000 max output tokens, so sentence-level annotation should not run into context limits under normal use. Still, implementation should keep prompts compact and avoid sending unnecessary article metadata.\r\n\r\nVLM image handling:\r\n- Do not send image URLs directly to the VLM.\r\n- Download the image, resize/compress if needed, convert it to base64, and send the base64 image input.\r\n- Reason: avoid leaking outlet/source information through image URLs and reduce shortcut bias.\r\n- Keep image_url only as internal metadata in the dataset, not inside the VLM prompt.\r\n\r\nRepository rules:\r\n- Do not use config.yaml.\r\n- Use .env for local secrets/runtime settings.\r\n- Commit .env.example.\r\n- Do not commit .env.\r\n- Add .env to .gitignore.\r\n- Include ai_usage/step_logs.md.\r\n- Every critical AI-assisted decision must be logged as a new step in ai_usage/step_logs.md.\r\n- Save prompts under prompts/.\r\n- README must mention that detailed sentence cleaning will be handled as a separate step.\r\n\r\nRequired outputs:\r\n- data/processed/articles.jsonl\r\n- data/processed/sentences.jsonl\r\n- data/processed/proxy_predictions.jsonl\r\n- data/processed/llm_annotations.jsonl\r\n- data/processed/vlm_annotations.jsonl\r\n- data/analysis/agreement_metrics.json\r\n- data/analysis/disagreement_examples.csv\r\n- README.md\r\n- prompts/\r\n- ai_usage/step_logs.md\r\n\r\nAnalysis plan:\r\n1. Dataset overview: article count, sentence count, outlet/block distribution, image availability.\r\n2. Proxy distribution: OBJ/SUBJ overall and by outlet block.\r\n3. LLM distribution: objective/subjective_framing overall and by outlet block.\r\n4. Agreement analysis: confusion matrix, precision, recall, F1, Cohen’s kappa using LLM as silver/reference labels.\r\n5. Disagreement analysis: proxy false positives and false negatives.\r\n6. Sentence length analysis: short/medium/long buckets vs subjectivity.\r\n7. VLM analysis: visual framing label distribution and image/text examples.\r\n8. Optional rationale/token analysis later.\r\n\r\nImportant wording:\r\n- Do not call LLM labels “gold labels”; call them silver/reference annotations.\r\n- Do not claim outlet block differences are causal.\r\n- Do not claim subjectivity equals bias.\r\n- Do not overclaim classifier accuracy.",
