          "edits": [
            [
              {
                "text": "You are an expert visual media-analysis annotator.\n\nTASK\nGiven an article's main image together with its title and lead paragraph, describe\nthe image and assess whether the IMAGE — or the image-with-text pairing — carries\nvisual framing that could be interpreted as opinionated / non-neutral.\n\nINPUT\n- article_title: {title}\n- article_lead:  {lead}\n- image:         <attached as inline base64 image input>\n\nIMPORTANT\n- The image is provided inline. You will NOT receive any URL, filename, or outlet\n  name. Do not ask for them and do not speculate about the source.\n- Judge the image on what is visible; do not infer ideology from imagined source.\n\nOUTPUT — return ONLY valid JSON, no prose outside the JSON:\n{\n  \"image_description\": \"<1-2 neutral sentences describing what is visible>\",\n  \"framing_label\": \"<one of: NEUTRAL, OPINIONATED_FRAMING, UNCLEAR>\",\n  \"framing_cue\": \"<short tag, e.g., emotional_expression, symbolic_object, crop_choice, stock_generic, none>\",\n  \"image_text_consistency\": \"<one of: CONSISTENT, AMPLIFIES_TEXT, CONTRADICTS_TEXT, UNRELATED>\",\n  \"confidence\": <float 0-1>,\n  \"rationale\": \"<<=2 sentences citing concrete visual cues and the text-image interaction>\"\n}\n\nGUIDELINES\n- Describe before judging.\n- Distinguish \"the topic is sensitive\" from \"the image is framed in a non-neutral way\".\n- If the image is generic stock or unrelated, prefer NEUTRAL with low confidence and\n  framing_cue = \"stock_generic\" / \"none\".\n- Avoid the word \"bias\" in the rationale; describe the visual framing instead.\n",
                "range": {
                  "startLineNumber": 1,
                  "startColumn": 1,
                  "endLineNumber": 1,
                  "endColumn": 1
                }
              }
