                "text": "\"\"\"Step: annotate_vlm — VLM annotation of article main images.\n\nModel: OpenAI gpt-5.4-mini (vision mode; verified 2026-06-01 — image input supported).\n\nImage handling rules (see CLAUDE.md Rule 6):\n    - Do NOT send image URLs to the model.\n    - Download the image locally (cached under data/raw/images/), optionally\n      resize/compress to a reasonable max edge (e.g., 1024 px) and re-encode to JPEG.\n    - base64-encode the bytes and pass as inline image input.\n    - image_url stays as DATASET METADATA only; it never appears in the prompt.\n\nPrompt: prompts/vlm_image_annotation.txt\n\nInput  : data/processed/articles.jsonl (uses title + lead + image_url -> local file)\nOutput : data/processed/vlm_annotations.jsonl with schema:\n    {\n      \"article_id\":           str,\n      \"image_description\":    str,\n      \"framing_label\":        \"NEUTRAL\" | \"OPINIONATED_FRAMING\" | \"UNCLEAR\",\n      \"framing_cue\":          str,\n      \"image_text_consistency\": \"CONSISTENT\" | \"AMPLIFIES_TEXT\" | \"CONTRADICTS_TEXT\" | \"UNRELATED\",\n      \"vlm_confidence\":       float,\n      \"vlm_rationale\":        str,\n      \"vlm_model\":            \"gpt-5.4-mini\",\n      \"vlm_snapshot\":         str | None\n    }\n\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nVLM_MODEL = \"gpt-5.4-mini\"\nMAX_IMAGE_EDGE_PX = 1024\n\n\ndef main() -> None:\n    raise NotImplementedError(\"annotate_vlm.py: implement download -> resize -> base64 -> VLM call\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n",
