                "text": "\"\"\"Step: analyze — EDA + proxy/LLM agreement analysis.\n\nRequired outputs:\n    data/analysis/agreement_metrics.json       # confusion matrix + precision/recall/F1 + Cohen's kappa\n    data/analysis/disagreement_examples.csv    # proxy FPs and FNs vs LLM reference\n\nAlso produces (used by notebooks/eda.ipynb):\n    - summary_tables.csv         (overview, distributions per outlet block)\n    - llm_rationale_terms.csv    (token frequency in LLM rationales)\n    - proxy_occlusion_terms.csv  (optional, deferred)\n    - figures/                   (sentence-length vs subjectivity, etc.)\n\nReminders:\n    - LLM labels are SILVER, not gold.\n    - Outlet-block differences are DESCRIPTIVE, never causal.\n    - Subjectivity is a PROXY for one facet of opinionated framing, not \"bias\".\n\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\n\ndef main() -> None:\n    raise NotImplementedError(\"analyze.py: implement after annotation outputs exist\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n",
